.TH "GAMEPAD.CONNECTED" "3JS" "December 27, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Gamepad.connected \- Gamepad: connected property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Gamepad.connected\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]Gamepad\f[R] interface returns a boolean indicating whether the
gamepad is still connected to the system.
.PP
If the gamepad is connected, the value is \f[CR]true\f[R]; if not, it is
\f[CR]false\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A boolean.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] gp = navigator.getGamepads()[0];
console.log(gp.connected);
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
Using the Gamepad API
